# Linux Basics – Essential Commands

## Objective
Practice foundational Linux commands commonly used in system administration and troubleshooting.

## Environment
- Linux (Red Hat–based distribution)
- Terminal / command line

## Commands Practiced
- pwd – display current directory
- ls – list files and directories
- cd – change directories
- mkdir – create directories
- rmdir – remove empty directories
- touch – create files
- cp – copy files
- mv – move or rename files
- rm – delete files
- cat – view file contents
- less – paginate file output
- man – access manual pages

## What I Did
- Navigated the filesystem using the command line
- Created and removed files and directories
- Viewed and managed file contents
- Used manual pages to understand command options

## Outcome
Built confidence using Linux command-line tools for everyday administrative tasks.
